From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mincore local analysis <not-for-submission@example.invalid>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 19:10:00 +0000
Subject: [test patch, not for submission] mm/mincore: check present PTEs
 before none/marker path

mincore_pte_range() currently checks the none/marker case before the
present-PTE path.  For the common resident anonymous base-page case, this
means every PTE first pays the none/marker tests before reaching the hot
present path and pte_batch_hint().

Local x86/QEMU lab measurements for a MADV_NOHUGEPAGE anonymous 64 MiB
mincore scan show that this branch layout is a large cost in v6.18.19 and
v7.0.9.  Moving the present-PTE branch first, while still preserving
pte_batch_hint() batching for batch > 1, improved the workload by roughly
30-39% on v6.18.19 and 33-38% on v7.0.9 across QEMU_SMP=1/2/4.  The
same test's THP/no-THP semantic smoke stayed valid.

This is a local test patch that documents the candidate shape.  It is not
ready for direct submission.  Before upstreaming, it still needs architecture
review of pte_present() vs marker/swap encodings, a real Signed-off-by, and
large-folio/mTHP preservation checks.
---
 mm/mincore.c | 21 +++++++++++----------
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/mincore.c b/mm/mincore.c
index 000000000000..000000000000 100644
--- a/mm/mincore.c
+++ b/mm/mincore.c
@@ -186,24 +186,25 @@ static int mincore_pte_range(pmd_t *pmd, unsigned long addr, unsigned long end,
 		pte_t pte = ptep_get(ptep);
 
 		step = 1;
-		/* We need to do cache lookup too for markers */
-		if (pte_none(pte) || pte_is_marker(pte))
-			__mincore_unmapped_range(addr, addr + PAGE_SIZE,
-						 vma, vec);
-		else if (pte_present(pte)) {
+		if (pte_present(pte)) {
 			unsigned int batch = pte_batch_hint(ptep, pte);
 
 			if (batch > 1) {
 				unsigned int max_nr = (end - addr) >> PAGE_SHIFT;
 
 				step = min_t(unsigned int, batch, max_nr);
+				for (i = 0; i < step; i++)
+					vec[i] = 1;
+			} else {
+				*vec = 1;
 			}
-
-			for (i = 0; i < step; i++)
-				vec[i] = 1;
+		/* We need to do cache lookup too for markers */
+		} else if (pte_none(pte) || pte_is_marker(pte)) {
+			__mincore_unmapped_range(addr, addr + PAGE_SIZE,
+						 vma, vec);
 		} else { /* pte is a swap entry */
 			const softleaf_t entry = softleaf_from_pte(pte);
 
 			*vec = mincore_swap(entry, false);
 		}
 		vec += step;
 	}
